data.name: Label5.Text
data.value:
Create easily your Minecraft server. Your Minecraft server can be hosted in both directions: Locally and in the Cloud. To play with outisde world, just open your port on the TCP protocol (default: 25565).
Create with: .Net framework 4.5 Programming language: VB.NET
Thanks to the sites: Github: for hosted software and all other information. getbukkit.org: for downloading API minecraft server. ipify.org: to receive the router's ipv4 in RAW format.
